            "metadata": {
                "abstract": "We describe a new open-source program called LEVERSC to address the challenges of visualizing the multi-channel 3-D images prevalent in biological microscopy. LEVERSC uses a custom WebGL hardware-accelerated raycasting engine unique in its combination of rendering quality and performance, particularly for multi-channel data. Key features include platform independence, quantitative visualization through interactive voxel localization, and reproducible dynamic visualization via the scripting interface. LEVERSC is fully scriptable and interactive, and works with MATLAB, Python and Java/ImageJ.",
